{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"attribute","text":"nonisolated"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"tint"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"_"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"internalParam","text":"tint"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ColorV","text":"Color","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"kind":"text","text":"?) -> "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"some"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewP","text":"View","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/View"},{"kind":"text","text":"\n"}]}]},{"kind":"parameters","parameters":[{"name":"tint","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tint "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/Color"},{"type":"text","text":" to apply."}]}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Discussion","anchor":"discussion"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use this method to override the default accent color for this view.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Unlike an app’s accent color, which can be overridden by user","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"preference, the tint color is always respected and should be used as a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"way to provide additional meaning to the control.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This example shows Answer and Decline buttons with "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/green","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/OpenSwiftUI\/documentation\/OpenSwiftUI\/ShapeStyle\/red","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" tint colors, respectively."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["struct ControlTint: View {","    var body: some View {","        HStack {","            Button {","                \/\/ Answer the call","            } label: {","                Label(\"Answer\", systemImage: \"phone\")","            }","            .tint(.green)","            Button {","                \/\/ Decline the call","            } label: {","                Label(\"Decline\", systemImage: \"phone.down\")","            }","            .tint(.red)","        }","        .buttonStyle(.borderedProminent)","        .padding()","    }","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Some controls adapt to the tint color differently based on their style,","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the current platform, and the surrounding context. For example, in","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"macOS, a button with the ","type":"text"},{"code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/bordered","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" style doesn’t","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"tint its background, but one with the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"PrimitiveButtonStyle\/borderedProminent","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" style does. In macOS, neither","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"of these button styles tint their label, but they do in other platforms.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"metadata":{"symbolKind":"method","externalID":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore4ViewPAAE4tintyQrAA5ColorVSgF::SYNTHESIZED::s:11OpenSwiftUI6ButtonV","extendedModule":"OpenSwiftUICore","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"tint","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"Color","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:15OpenSwiftUICore5ColorV"}